Subject: Re: [T2] What is the diff between 1700 and 1800 case?

At 05:17 AM 10/1/2002, Vanagon man wrote:
>I know crank and rods are the same......Is the case bored different for
>different cylinders?  Or will 1800 cylinders fit a 1700 case and vice/versa?

There is no significant difference between a 1700 case and an 1800 case and you can use either size cylinders in either case without modification.  You can also use 2-liter pistons/rods/crankshaft in a 1700/1800 case without modifications.

-David
